PROCUREMENT PROCEDURES GUIDE
Purpose: This guide establishes procedures for the procurement of goods and services. Request Initiation: Departments must submit purchase requisitions for required items. Supplier Selection: At least three quotations should be obtained for significant purchases. Approval Process: Procurement requests must receive authorization from management
before purchase. Receiving and Inspection: Purchased items must be inspected upon delivery. Documentation: Procurement records should be retained for audit and compliance
purposes.
